[Lamontagne Chocolate, Chocolate From Canada, Chocolate Lovers, Chocolate Goals, DryFruit Delight, Chocolate Covered Goodness]

I’m the type of wife who will help my husband look for his chocolate…
…that I already ate. 🤫

Once chocolate enters our house, let’s be real….it’s mine. That’s just how it works around here.  Especially when it’s LaMontagne Chocolate.

These Triple Chocolate Cookie Bites are one of my new faves…
but I got totally hooked because of their chocolate-covered pistachios with Himalayan sea salt. OBSESSED.
And no, I didn’t share. Not even one. 😂

LaMontagne Chocolate is a Canadian, family-owned company that’s been crafting premium chocolate in Quebec for over 40 years—using high-quality ingredients and creating moments to seriously savor.

🛍 You can usually find them at Marshalls, HomeGoods, or TJ Maxx. And they’re back on Amazon in October, so stock up if you see them!
